The paper deals with Delaunay triangulations, which are a fundamental topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The stability of these triangulations is studied, which involves analyzing the behavior of the triangulation under perturbations, making it relevant to the sub-categories of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also introduces a parametrized notion of genericity for Delaunay triangulations, which is a concept that is commonly studied in discrete and combinatorial geometry (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper discusses the thickness of Delaunay simplices, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and geometric reasoning (cs.GR).
